==English==

===Etymology===
From late Latin ''[[palilogia]]'', from Greek [[παλιλογια]], from [[παλιν]] ‘again’ + [[−λογια]] ‘pertaining to speech, discourse’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pə'lɪləʤi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|palillog|ies}}

# emphatic [[repetition]] of a word or phrase

